==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metaphysical
<hw>Met`a*phys"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧taphysique</ets>. See <er>Metaphysics</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to metaphysics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>According to rules or principles of metaphysics;
<as>as, <ex>metaphysical</ex> reasoning</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Preternatural or supernatural.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The golden round⟦br⟧
Which fate and metaphysical aid doth seem⟦br⟧
To have thee crowned withal.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metaphysically</ent>⟦br⟧
